In this article, President Trump delivers a speech during a Memorial Day ceremony to honor fallen soldiers. He expresses gratitude to the military and their families for their sacrifices and acknowledges the pain and loss experienced by Gold Star families. The President highlights the bravery and heroism of specific individuals who lost their lives in service, including Secretary John Kelly's son and Specialist Christopher Horton. He also pays tribute to Senator Bob Dole and his service in World War II. The President emphasizes the importance of remembering and honoring those who made the ultimate sacrifice for freedom. He concludes by expressing his love and support for the military and the United States.